message:
The recurring (cron) scheduler has not emitted a heartbeat in 15 minutes. The leader-elected ticker is likely down or wedged, so NO recurring schedules are firing (the per-schedule stale monitor may not fire if nothing is sweeping).

Runbook:
1. Confirm at least one process has `recurring_scheduler_enabled: true` and is running.
2. Check the Redis leader lock `kafka_batch:cron:leader_lock` — a dead holder should expire within its TTL.
3. Check daemon/worker logs for `[kbatch-cron] recurring scheduler ...`.

{{#is_alert}}No recurring-scheduler heartbeat in 15m.{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_no_data}}No recurring-scheduler heartbeat data at all.{{/is_no_data}}
@CHANGE_ME

A job could not be added to a batch because the batch was already sealed/terminal or cancelled. Usually the 'create-sealed-then-push' race: a batch created without a block form finalized after the first job, so later PushJob calls were rejected and those jobs were dropped.

Runbook:
1. Prefer the block form of CreateBatch (seal only after all jobs are enqueued).
2. Check the producer for ignored BatchClosedError around the affected batch_id/job_type.

{{#is_alert}}Push rejections observed in the last 15m.{{/is_alert}}
@CHANGE_ME
